<br>
Second, I have no association with the 1st Fist of Light other than talking to banegrivm on ICQ and via email concerning the board.  I have openly stated I am available to talk to anyone in this community via icq or email.  He contacted me and gave me his thoughts, but then again many people have sent me an email and I have no qualms about answering anyone's emails or talking with them on icq.  I have never heard of 1st Fist of Light before this community board was opened, nor do I know anyone in that particular guild on a personal note.  I honestly don't even know what server they were on before they showed up here.<br>
<br>
Third, I rethought my decision to add the tavern, and I did think it was a good idea and I was open to the suggestion.  I will admit I did not think it out well, and I realized after reading the initial posts that I had made a mistake in sanctioning a guild sponsoring a forum here.  I was only thinking of the community first, and not anyone's personal agendas.  I happen to think that the idea of people handing out prizes in game is a nice idea to people who have good stories.  I understand that I should have given the opportunity for any guild to sponsor an item/monetary prize for participating in the community forums for storytelling.  If any guild wants to offer a prize for the month and pick out a story they like then please contact me.<br>
<br>
I also realized and talked it over with my husband about the issue, and we both agreed that it wasn't right to post a link to their guild page because it was more of a promotion, but if that guild is offering a reward for a story, I felt that some notice should be given for who is going to hand out a prize.  I think its vital that a server community should get involved in doing things to promote community spirit.  Another reasoning I had was that yes they could go to the 1st Fist of Light guild's board and post stories there, but some people would not like to have to go to different ezboards to post original work, where they could post one and have more people read it since people would come here before they go looking around and reading individual guild boards.  Writers would get more *publicity* on a general board that has more traffic than an individual guild board.<br>
<br>
To me, its not about showing favoritism or biased towards one guild, but more of someone saying &quot;hey I want the community to have more options to get together and express themselves in written work and to be honest, quite a few people would like to be rewarded with cash or items in game for sharing their work.  When Banegrivm approached me with the idea, and honestly it was not his original idea but someone else in his guild, it really showed to me that people were interested in promoting community growth and spirit.<br>
<br>
I uphold my opinion that it was and is a nice concept and was made with the best intentions for the community rather than for an individual or group.  Giving credit with a link for the idea and for the people who want to give away their in game earnings and loot seems only fair, since I did not think of the idea, nor did I suggest handing out prizes in game.<br>
<br>
By deleting your double posts and moving the original post was not in anyway trying to censor.  I locked the post since I thought of a compromise to make the forum moderated by all the moderators and taking out any links, other than the recognition that the 1st Fist of Light would hand out a prize, would be sufficient as a way to promote harmony and not start a big huge thread.<br>
<br>
I feel that I am a fair person, and I will be the first person to say I have and do and will make mistakes.  So I am sorry that I did make a person(s) feel that I was being biased and showing any type of favortism because that was not my intention or desire to do so.<br>
<br>
I hope this post of mine has cleared up some of the confusion and shown what I have felt about this issue.  I would offer the suggestion, and this is for Bane and for Zann and any other guilds, that if you would like to sponsor a prize once a month for the best story telling we could work out a system of rotation and whoever is handing out a prize for that month could be given recognition for their community service.<br>
<br>
