You wanna see an example of basically what Jaxy was doing. Checkout here:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://forums.prounreal.com">Prounreal Forums</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Prounreal is a major community forum for the UT game. Prounreal hosts clan forums. That does *not* mean they are showing &quot;favoritism&quot;. Some of those clans are *the* best in the game, some are not so great.<br>
<br>
Why do it that way? It helps *create a community*.<br>
<br>
Instead of having forums spread all over the net, you can go to one or two locations and read a lot of the happenings for the game/server/world/etc.<br>
<br>
Could Jaxy host *all* guilds from FV? Certainly not, just like I can't host ALL guilds' websites on my server.<br>
<br>
It should be first come-first serve until a number of spots are filled.<br>
